<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="579" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d579">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-12-02"><hi rend="italic">December 2,
                                1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Our consul-general at Havana has telegraphed that the custom-house has
                            embargoed $3,000 worth of sugar belonging to Hidalgo &amp; Co., to pay
                            fines. The fines imposed upon the Ward Line of steamers are for mere
                            clerical errors in manifests from which Spanish vessels in our ports are
                            exempt. Ask that intendente be requested by telegraph to report facts to
                            Madrid for decision. Inform Department by cable of action taken.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gresham.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>